The most naive natives are still waiting on the shore for a ship with a load of glass beads, for which they have already paid the treacherous merchants with gold bars. But even they are less naive than other natives who believe that the merchants will not just sail, but will crawl on their knees and return the stolen 300 billion green papers, because the oil and gas on the island are the best in the world, and without them, the merchants simply cannot. ..